'''Bloody show''' is the passage of a small amount of [[blood]] or blood-tinged [[mucus]] through the [[vagina]] near the end of [[pregnancy]]. It is caused by the detachment of the [[cervical mucus plug]] that seals the cervix during pregnancy,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medlineplus.gov/ency/presentations/100198_2.htm|title=Vaginal birth - series&mdash;Indications: MedlinePlus Medical Encyclopedia|website=medlineplus.gov|language=en|access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref> and is one of the signs that [[Childbirth|labor]] may be imminent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medlineplus.gov/ency/patientinstructions/000508.htm|title=Am I in labor?: MedlinePlus Medical Encyclopedia|website=medlineplus.gov|language=en|access-date=2018-10-17}}</ref> Although the bloody show is a common and harmless cause of bleeding in late pregnancy, there are many other possible causes for vaginal bleeding, some of which may indicate serious medical problems such as [[miscarriage]] or [[placental abruption]], and vaginal bleeding should not be ignored as a possible sign of serious complications.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=McKennett|first=M|last2=Fullerton|first2=JT|date=1995/02|title=Vaginal bleeding in pregnancy.|url=https://europepmc.org/abstract/med/7863960|journal=American Family Physician|language=en|volume=51|issue=3|issn=0002-838X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/pregnancy-and-baby/vaginal-bleeding-pregnant/|title=Vaginal bleeding in pregnancy|website=nhs.uk|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-10-17|date=2017-12-21}}</ref> 

